  "riddle": "1. In the world of melodic kinship, a duo named after a bird began their musical journey. In what year did they take flight?    \n\n2. A legendary band, known for their intricate harmonies and surfing themes, had a number of vocalists joining in unison. How many souls sang together at once in their most celebrated moments?    \n\n3. If you wandered close to the echo of harmonies, what is the count of places of worship found in proximity?    \n\n4. Once a cornerstone in the music industry, which record label emerged in the midst of the Great Depression? What year marks its establishment?    \n\n5. Take the year you uncovered from the previous step and play with its digits by reversing them. What fresh number do you obtain in this transposition?    \n\n6. Now, the final piece awaits. From the values in clue 4 and clue 5, compute the result of the expression: (clue 4 + clue 5) % 10. The answer shall be a single digit, revealing the essence of your quest.",
